{"article_id":"7Y5X7KuSlyaCm6aO","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Senate passed legislation Wednesday","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"that would make it less expensive for college students to borrow money","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to pay for classes , housing and books .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"But interest rates could soon start climbing .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"The proposal ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"that passed by 81 votes to 18 ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"would link interest rates on federal student loans to the financial markets .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"That means student loans for the next few years would have lower interest rates .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"Higher rates would come in later years","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"if the economy improves","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"as expected .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Liberal Democrats opposed the White House-backed proposal as a bait-and-switch measure","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"that would lure in new borrowers .","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Republicans supported the measure","depth":6},{"id":14,"text":"and helped the bill win passage .","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"The bill is similar to one","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"the House has already passed .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"The White House and its allies said","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"the new loan structure would offer lower rates to 11 million borrowers right away","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"and save the average undergraduate $ 1,500 in interest","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"But there was no denying","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"the new structure could cost future students","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"if the economy improves","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"as expected","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"and interest rates climb .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"The White House 's allies instead suggested","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"the new formula is better than the status quo .","depth":6},{"id":27,"text":"After the bill ' s passage the White House released a statement from President Obama","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"applauding the vote .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"\" This compromise is a major victory for our nation 's students , \"","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"the statement read .","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"\" It meets the key principles","depth":7},{"id":32,"text":"I laid out from the start :","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"it locks in low rates next year ,","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"and it does n't overcharge students to pay down the deficit .","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"I urge the House to pass this bill","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"so that I can sign it into law right away ,","depth":5},{"id":37,"text":"and I hope","depth":5},{"id":38,"text":"both parties build on this progress","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"by taking even more steps","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"to bring down soaring costs","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"and keep a good education","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"- a cornerstone","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"of what it means to be middle class -","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"within reach for working families . \"","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"Rates on subsidized Stafford loans doubled to 6.8 percent July 1","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"because Congress could not agree on a way","depth":6},{"id":47,"text":"to keep them at 3.4 percent .","depth":6},{"id":48,"text":"Liberal members of the Democratic caucus were vocal in their opposition over the potentially shifting rates","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"included in the Senate measure ,","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"which passed with support from both parties .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"The bill passed with support from 45 Republicans , 35 Democrats and Sen. Angus King , the independent from Maine","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"who helped negotiate the deal .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Sen. Mike Lee , R-Utah , joined 16 Democrats and Sen. Bernie Sanders , the Vermont independent","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"who caucuses with Democrats ,","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"to oppose the legislation .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Sen. Claire McCaskill , D-Mo. , did not cast a recorded vote .","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"`` This permanent , market-based plan makes students ' loans cheaper , simpler and more certain , ''","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"said Sen. Lamar Alexander , the top Republican on the Senate education panel .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"`` It ends the annual game of Congress playing politics with student loan interest rates at the expense of students","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"planning their futures . ''","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"Under the bipartisan deal , undergraduates this fall could borrow at a 3.9 percent interest rate .","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Graduate students would have access to loans at 5.4 percent ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"and parents could borrow at 6.4 percent .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"Those rates would rise","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"as the economy picks up","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"and it becomes more expensive for the government to borrow money .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"The compromise could be a good deal for students through the 2015 academic year .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"After that , interest rates are expected to climb above where they were","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"when students left campus in the spring ,","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"if congressional estimates prove correct .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"As part of the compromise , Democrats won a protection for students","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"by capping rates at a maximum 8.25 percent for undergraduates .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"Graduate students would not pay rates higher than 9.5 percent ,","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"and parents ' rates would top out at 10.5 percent .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"Using Congressional Budget Office estimates ,","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"rates would not reach those limits in the next 10 years .","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"But even among those","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"who voted for it ,","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"frustrations remained evident .","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"`` The bill","depth":6},{"id":81,"text":"that is before us","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"represents a number of compromises","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"that were made on both sides , ''","depth":6},{"id":84,"text":"said Sen. Tom Harkin , the Iowa Democrat","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"who chairs the Senate Health , Education , Labor and Pensions Committee ,","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"before the vote .","depth":5},{"id":87,"text":"Harkin said","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"the legislation is not what he would have written","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"if he had the final say","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"but he also said","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"that he recognizes the need","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"to restore the lower rates on students","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"before they return to campus for classes .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"`` It 's the best","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"that we can do , ''","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"Harkin said on the Senate floor .","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"`` If we do n't pass this today ,","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"there will be one sure effect :","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"student loans will be almost twice what they would be under this bill . ''","depth":9},{"id":100,"text":"Most Senate Republicans","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"who pushed for interest rates to be linked to the financial markets","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"voted for the measure .","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"It was negotiated by Democratic Sen. Joe Manchin of West Virginia and GOP Sens . Richard Burr of North Carolina and Lamar Alexander of Tennessee , the top Republican on the Senate Health , Education , Labor and Pensions Committee .","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"`` They may come from different political parties ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"but they all really care about students .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"And this bill proves it , ''","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"said Senate Republican leader Mitch McConnell of Kentucky .","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"`` And there 's something else","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"this bill proves , too :","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"That Democrats can work with Republicans","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"when they actually want to do it --","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"when they check their partisan , take-it-or-leave-it approaches at the door","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"and actually talk with , rather than at , us . ''","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"The compromise","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"negotiated in the Senate","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"closely hews to what House Republicans passed this year ,","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"and that 's a sticking point for some liberals .","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"Sen. Jack Reed , D-R.I. , pushed for an extension of the current 3.4 percent rate","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"so lawmakers could address the subject this fall during the revision of the Higher Education Act .","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"Sen. Elizabeth Warren , D-Mass. , has objected to students paying higher interest rates","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"than the Federal Reserve offers to big banks .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"`` I understand","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"that compromise is n't always pretty ,","depth":14},{"id":124,"text":"but there is n't any compromise in this bill , ''","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"Warren said last week","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"when the deal was announced .","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"`` In fact , I think","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"the whole system stinks , ''","depth":13},{"id":129,"text":"she added during a Senate speech .","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"Sens . Patty Murray , D-Wash. , and Al Franken , D-Minn. , planned amendments","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"that would redirect any profits","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"made through the bill","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"to help low-income students .","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"The Congressional Budget Office estimated","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"the bill","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"as written","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"would reduce the deficit by $ 715 million over the next decade .","depth":12},{"id":138,"text":"During that same time , federal loans would be a $ 1.4 trillion program .","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"`` We 've got to get out of the business","depth":12},{"id":140,"text":"of making profits of struggling families","depth":13},{"id":141,"text":"who want nothing more","depth":14},{"id":142,"text":"than to be able to send their kids to college , ''","depth":14},{"id":143,"text":"said Sen. Bernie Sanders , a Vermont independent","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"who caucuses with Democrats .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"`` This legislation only makes a bad situation worse . ''","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":291,"left":190,"right":290,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":190,"left":172,"right":189,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":172,"left":156,"right":171,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":149,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":149,"left":148,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":148,"left":0,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":155,"left":151,"right":154,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":150,"right":6,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":150,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":7,"right":153,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":153,"left":8,"right":152,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"mode","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":171,"left":159,"right":170,"relat